==Norwegian==
===Adjective===
[[Category:Norwegian adjectives]]
{{no-adj-3}}
#[[off#Adjective|off]]; not operating
#: ''å sla av'' -- ''to turn off''

===Preposition===
[[Category:Norwegian prepositions]]
'''av'''
#[[from]]
#:''I got it from…'' = ''Jeg fikk den av…''
#[[by]]; ''in construction of the passive tense''
#:''The house was painted by him'' = ''Huset ble malt av ham''
#[[of]]
#:''It is made of wood'' = ''Det er laget av tre''

----
==Swedish==
===Preposition===
'''av'''

#[[from]] 
#:''It follows from...'' = ''Det följer av...''
#[[by]]; ''in construction of the passive tense''
#:''The house was painted by him'' = ''Huset målades av honom''
#[[of]]
#:''It is made of wood'' = ''Den är gjord av trä''
#Short form of [[avstängd]] (=[[shut down]])


#[[broken]] 
#:''The rope is broken'' = ''Repet är av'' (to make a statement about its present condition), (or) ''Repet har gått av'' (to make a statement about what has happened to it)

===Expressions===
#[[lasta av]]
#:unload (concerning transportations)
#[[stänga av]]
#:[[shut down]]
#[[stänga av någon]] (''e.g. in sports'')
#:to [[ban]] someone, to [[prohibit]] a person from participating in e.g. a competition; or from school 
#[[lägga av]]
#:stop doing (something), [[cease doing]] (something)

